ard for IACS service provider security requirements."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Temporal Score Adjustments","description":"Regularly updating CVSS temporal scores (e.g., exploit availability) for ICS vulnerabilities. Supports DM-3's dynamic severity analysis requirement.","related_links":[{"title":"ICS-CERT Advisories","url":"https://www.cisa.gov/uscert/ics/advisories","description":"CISA's ICS advisories with temporal scoring examples."},{"title":"Yokogawa Security Bulletin","url":"https://web-material3.yokogawa.com/SecurityBulletinList.html","description":"Vendor example of temporal score updates."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Compensating Controls Mapping","description":"Documenting how existing controls affect CVSS exploitability scores. Essential for DM-3 compliance when mitigation reduces severity.","related_links":[{"title":"ABB Security Advisory Process","url":"https://global.abb/group/en/about/technology/security","description":"ABB's method for evaluating control impacts."},{"title":"NIST SP 800-82r3","url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-82/rev-3/final","description":"ICS security guide with control effectiveness guidance."}]}],"name":"Assessing security-related issues","description":"A process shall be employed for analysing security-related issues in the product to include: b) severity as defined by a vulnerability scoring system (for example, CVSS);","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"To systematically evaluate the severity of vulnerabilities and prioritize remediation efforts based on standardized scoring systems.","methodologies":[{"name":"CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System)","description":"A framework for rating the severity of security vulnerabilities in software. It provides a numerical score (0-10) representing the severity, which can be translated into qualitative representations (e.g., Low, Medium, High, Critical)."},{"name":"STRIDE","description":"A threat modeling methodology that helps identify potential threats (Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, Elevation of Privilege) and assess their impact on the system."}],"tools":[{"name":"NIST National Vulnerability Database (NVD)","purpose":"Provides CVSS scores for known vulnerabilities, aiding in the assessment of severity and impact."},{"name":"Qualys Vulnerability Management","purpose":"Automates vulnerability scanning and assessment, integrating CVSS scores for prioritization."}],"case_study":{"example":"A power plant's DCS (Distributed Control System) was assessed using CVSS to prioritize vulnerabilities. A critical vulnerability (CVSS 9.8) in a PLC firmware was identified and patched before exploitation could occur."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"To ensure that vulnerability severity assessments are consistently applied and documented, aligning with IEC 62443-4-1 requirements.","audit_checklist":["Verify that CVSS or an equivalent scoring system is used for all identified vulnerabilities.","Check that severity scores are documented and reviewed by the security team.","Ensure that remediation efforts are prioritized based on severity scores."],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of vulnerabilities assessed using CVSS or equivalent","target":"100%"},{"kpi":"Average time to remediate vulnerabilities by severity level (Critical, High, Medium, Low)","target":"Critical: <7 days, High: <30 days, Medium: <90 days, Low: <180 days"}],"compliance_procedure":"Document the CVSS scoring process in the security policy, including roles responsible for assessment and review. Maintain records of all vulnerability assessments and remediation actions."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure personnel are proficient in using vulnerability scoring systems and interpreting their results.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Fundamentals Specialist","description":"Covers foundational knowledge of ICS security, including vulnerability assessment and scoring."},{"name":"GIAC Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional (GICSP)","description":"Provides training on ICS security practices, including vulnerability management and CVSS."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of personnel competency in vulnerability assessment, including practical exercises using CVSS."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To streamline the vulnerability assessment process and ensure consistency in severity scoring.","tools":[{"name":"Tenable Nessus","purpose":"Automates vulnerability scanning and provides CVSS scores for identified vulnerabilities."},{"name":"Rapid7 InsightVM","purpose":"Integrates CVSS scoring and prioritization into vulnerability management workflows."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate vulnerability scanning tools with the DevSecOps pipeline to automatically assess and score vulnerabilities during development and deployment phases."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy systems may not support modern vulnerability assessment tools or patching mechanisms, requiring alternative approaches.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network Segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to limit exposure and reduce the impact of vulnerabilities."},{"approach":"Compensating Controls","description":"Implement additional security measures (e.g., intrusion detection systems) to mitigate vulnerabilities that cannot be patched."}],"example_policy":"Legacy systems must be documented with their vulnerabilities and compensating controls. CVSS scores should still be calculated, and risks must be reviewed annually."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective vulnerability management requires collaboration between security, engineering, and management teams.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for Vulnerability Management","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Assess and score vulnerabilities using CVSS."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Implement patches or mitigations based on severity."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve resource allocation for remediation efforts."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A cross-functional committee reviews conflicting priorities (e.g., patching vs. system availability) and makes decisions based on risk assessment."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"Vulnerability assessment practices must evolve to address new threats and lessons learned.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor Threat Intelligence","description":"Subscribe to CISA alerts and ICS-CERT advisories for updates on new vulnerabilities and threats."},{"step":"Review Incident Reports","description":"Analyze security incidents to identify gaps in vulnerability assessment processes."}],"lessons_learned":"After a ransomware attack on an ICS, the organization updated its policy to include mandatory CVSS scoring for all vulnerabilities, regardless of perceived risk."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-15"} 
