echnology (OT) risks, such as firmware vulnerabilities or protocol weaknesses, that may propagate across product lines."}],"tools":[{"name":"NIST 800-30 (ICS Adaptation)","purpose":"Guides risk assessments for identifying shared vulnerabilities in ICS product families."},{"name":"Vulnerability databases (e.g., CVE, ICS-CERT)","purpose":"Cross-references reported issues with internal product inventories."}],"case_study":{"example":"A power plant DCS vendor identified a shared cryptographic weakness in controller firmware versions 2.x-4.x, enabling coordinated patching."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"Ensures systematic tracking of security issues across product lineages as required by IEC 62443-4-1.","audit_checklist":["Evidence of cross-product vulnerability mapping procedures","Records of shared component analysis (e.g., common libraries, firmware)","Documented justification for excluded products/versions"],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of product versions assessed for shared issues","target":"100% of supported versions"},{"kpi":"Mean time to identify affected products","target":"<72 hours from initial detection"}],"compliance_procedure":"Maintain a product lineage database with versioned components, automated against CVE feeds, reviewed quarterly by the security team."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"Technical staff must understand dependency chains and versioning impacts in ICS environments.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Certifications","description":"Covers secure development lifecycle requirements for product families (e.g., ISA 62443-4-1 Specialist)."},{"name":"GICSP","description":"Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional training includes ICS vulnerability management."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual practical test analyzing a simulated multi-product vulnerability scenario."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"Automation is critical for scalable analysis across product versions in large